I’m Afrikaans. I’m African. And I’m done pretending our future lies anywhere but here. If we want to protect our language, our culture, and our dignity — it has to be through unity with Africa, not distance from it. Afrikaans doesn’t survive by isolating — it survives by standing proudly, shoulder to shoulder, with every African building a new future. This is where we belong.
